    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Everything thought proper has been done in behalf of Stern, who was nevertheless
                    sentenced to fine and imprisonment for two weeks. His only recourse, to appeal
                    or to petition for pardon, which, in the absence of instructions, embassy would
                    not feel at liberty to support.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jackson</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chargé</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
